title: SpaceX launches commercial mission to ISS
summary: SpaceX launched a Crew Dragon spacecraft April 8 carrying four commercial astronauts to the International Space Station for Axiom Space.

title: Axiom-1, the first ever private crewed mission to ISS, set for liftoff
summary: SpaceX and Axiom Space are set to launch the AX-1 mission to the International Space Station (ISS) on Friday, April 8, 2022, at 11:17:11 am EDST / 15:17:11 UTC from LC-39A at the Kennedy Space Center in Florida.
